707529f-a.text:
First Avenue (across view from riht to left,obscured by rooftops on the westerly side), from E. 20t (extreme right) to E. 23rd (extreme left) Streets, as viewed eastward from a loft structure at the S.E. corner of Second Avenue and E. 22nd Street. This area is better known as the "Gae Houuse" because of tanks and plants of the Gonsolidated Edison Go. and as such produced rany a Tarmmanyite. Most of this area was forrerlv under ater and subsequent fills for the new East River Drive will extend the line further. Across the East River apnears the Greennoint
sectionof Brooklyn.
Sentemher 2, 1929,
Views 1,2 and 3
~.L. Sperr
